				<h1>Holiday Clubs</h1>
				
				<p>Every year in August we hold a Summer Holiday Club for <strong>children of ages 5-11</strong>.</p><br />
				
				<p><strong>This year's club will be held from <em>13th to 16th August</em> - for more details see below.</strong></p><br />
				
				<!--<p>The club sessions take place from <strong>10am to 12 noon each day</strong> with a <strong>Grand Finale on the Friday beginning at 6pm</strong> to which families are invited. The whole club is <strong>free of charge</strong>, apart from tickets for food on the Friday evening which will be sold during the week of the club.</p>
				
				<p>Each year we have <strong>songs, games, quizzes, crafts, and more</strong>, so there's something for everyone.</p>

				<p>Details for next year's club will appear here when I get them!</p>-->

				<h1>Summer Holiday Club 2013</h1><br />
				
				<img src="images/hc_2013_logo.jpg" alt="Holiday Club 2013 Story Keepers" id="hclogo" width="610" height="344" /><br /><br />
				
				<div id="hcparagraphs">
					<p><strong>Our Holiday Club will run this year from Tuesday 13th August to Friday 16th August</strong>.<br />The <strong>sessions will be from 10am to 12 noon</strong> on all four mornings as usual, with a <strong>Grand Finale and buffet on Friday evening</strong>. Tickets for this are sold during the week.</p>
					
					<p><strong>"Story Keepers" was originally an animated children's TV series</strong> and re-tells events in the life of Jesus through the eyes of children living shortly afterwards, who have lots of fun and adventure at the expense of the Roman authorities!</p>
					
					<p>The club includes <strong>songs, quizzes, games, crafts, etc etc</strong>! <strong>Games are outdoors</strong> whenever weather allows, and <strong>safe footwear (eg trainers rather than flip-flops) is essential every day</strong>. Games on Friday morning will involve a certain amount of water, but if you do not want your child to get wet you can indicate this on the form below. We also include Holiday Club photographs (as can be seen below) on our website, and it is possible that your child's face might appear in one of these. Again, if you do not wish this to happen you can refuse permission on the form below.</p>
					
					<p><strong>Children aged 5-11 are welcome</strong> as mentioned above and, while not essential, it helps a lot if you register your child(ren) before the club begins, in order for us to assess the numbers likely to attend. You can do this by <strong>printing off and filling in the form below</strong> and posting it to us at the church or bringing it with you on the first morning that your child attends. <strong>All children must have the consent of a parent (or adult with legal parental responsibility)</strong>. It is <strong>essential that all of the details required on the form are filled in, using a separate form for each child</strong>.</p>
					
					<p>If you have any queries, please don't hesitate to <a href="mailto:paul@ferringbaptist.org.uk">contact us</a>!</p>
				</div>

				<p>-----------------</p>
				
				<p><strong>Form download: <a href="fbc_storykeepers_2013_registration.pdf">click here (PDF)</a></strong><br />
				(if the PDF pops up when you click the link, right click on the document that appears and click Print to print off a copy that you can then fill in)</p>
				
				<p>You can post the form to us or put it in our letter box if you live nearby - <a href="http://ferringbaptist.org.uk/visitors_location.php">click here for our address</a>.</p>
				
